I went ahead and jumped on this because I need it too.

I've tried a bunch of approaches to multi-file filtering and this seemed to be the best option because it:

- preserves all dependent rows (stops, stop times, etc.) of filtered trips
- abstracts away changes to the config graph
- doesn't add complexity to the feed class

```python
import partridge as ptg

_date, service_ids = ptg.read_busiest_date('gtfs.zip')

filters = {
    'trips.txt': {
        'service_id': service_ids,
    },
    'stop_times.txt': {
        'stop_id': '2541151',
        'stop_sequence': 5,
    },
}

feed = ptg.get_filtered_feed('TfNSW-2017-11-02.zip', filters)
```

In example part,   
vapid_claims={
                "sub": "YourNameHere@example.org",
            }
It will lead to an error which lacks "mailto" fields.

